I rate this 10/10.
Why I like this version
Unlike many security guides, it doesn't tie us to a specific vendor or product. Instead, it enforces enduring security principles:
•	Secure by default
•	Least privilege
•	Tenant isolation
•	Defense in depth
•	Privacy by design
•	OWASP alignment
•	Auditability
These principles will still be valid if, years from now, InverBrass moves from Supabase Auth to Microsoft Entra ID, Keycloak, Auth0, or another identity provider.
